==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puritanical
<hw>Pu`ri*tan"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
the Puritans, or to their doctrines and practice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Precise in observance of legal or religious
requirements; strict; overscrupulous; rigid; -- often used by way of
reproach or contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Paritanical</qex> circles, from which plays and novels were
strictly excluded.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had all the <qex>puritanic</qex> traits, both good and
evil.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puritanically</ent>⟦br⟧
